{"word":"G3083 - λύτρον - lýtron - loo'-tron - Ransom","slug":"G3083","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">λύτρον</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>lýtron"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>loo'-tron"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Ransom"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"- Original: <b><el>λύτρον</el></b> <p />- Transliteration: <b>Lutron</b> <p />- Phonetic: <b>loo'-tron</b> <p class=\"def\">- Definition: </p> <p class='li260'><b>1.</b> the price for redeeming, ransom </p> <p class='li520'><b>a.</b> paid for slaves, captives </p> <p class='li520'><b>b.</b> for the ransom of life </p> <p class='li260'><b>2.</b> to liberate many from misery and the penalty of their sins </p> <p class=\"origin\"/>- Origin: from <a href=\"#/G3089\">G3089</a> <p />- TDNT entry: 4:328 & 4:340,543 <p />- Part(s) of speech: Noun Neuter <p />- Strong's: From <a href=\"#/G3089\">G3089</a>; something to <i>loosen</i> with that is a redemption <i>price</i> (figuratively <i>atonement</i>): - ransom."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G179\">G179</a>, <a href=\"#/G1955\">G1955</a>, <a href=\"#/G1956\">G1956</a>, <a href=\"#/G2646\">G2646</a>, <a href=\"#/G2647\">G2647</a>, <a href=\"#/G3084\">G3084</a>, <a href=\"#/G3085\">G3085</a>, <a href=\"#/G3086\">G3086</a>, <a href=\"#/G3089\">G3089</a>, <a href=\"#/G359\">G359</a>, <a href=\"#/G360\">G360</a>, <a href=\"#/G487\">G487</a>, <a href=\"#/G629\">G629</a>, <a href=\"#/G630\">G630</a>"}]}